GPT Partition Entry

Field Documentation

UINT64 EFI_PARTITION_ENTRY::Attributes

Attribute bits, all bits reserved by UEFI Bit 0 Required for the platform to function. Bits 1-47 Undefined and must be zero. Bits 48-63 Reserved for GUID specific use.

EFI_LBA EFI_PARTITION_ENTRY::EndingLBA

Ending LBA of the partition defined by this entry.

CHAR16 EFI_PARTITION_ENTRY::PartitionName[36]

Unicode string.

EFI_GUID EFI_PARTITION_ENTRY::PartitionTypeGUID

Unique ID that defines the purpose and type of this Partition. A value of zero defines that this partition entry is not being used.

EFI_LBA EFI_PARTITION_ENTRY::StartingLBA

Starting LBA of the partition defined by this entry

EFI_GUID EFI_PARTITION_ENTRY::UniquePartitionGUID

GUID that is unique for every partition entry. Every partition ever created will have a unique GUID. This GUID must be assigned when the GUID Partition Entry is created.
